title: Dog-on-a-leash lemma
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Given two loops $$\gamma_0,\gamma_1\colon \sphere^1 \to \R^2 \setminus \{0\}$$ in the punctured plane, if
$$
\|\gamma_0(s) - \gamma_1(s)\| \le \|\gamma_0(s)\|
$$
for all $$s \in \sphere^1,$$ then $$\gamma_0 \simeq \gamma_1$$ in $$\R^2 \setminus \{0\}.$$